        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 5:14PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 514 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Twin Oaks, or near Independence, moving southeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Sparta...
Independence...
Bridle Creek...
Whitehead...
Stratford...
Twin Oaks...
and Piney Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
